comments.body:
@vors helped me to restructure the changes and commits. Thanks Sergei!
I will make sure group changes appropriately in future work.

@andschwa can you take a look again and see if you have any other concerns?
BTW, can I use the "merge pull request" button? Or should I merge it from CLI with "merge --ff"?

@vors There isn't a runtime specific way to set dependencies (yet?). It was supposed to hit `dotnet` RTM but we're unsure if it will. However, if PowerShell ships with LocalAccounts, then probably the best thing we can do is throw platform not supported until if/when these are implemented.

The alternative (and ugly) work-around is to `#if !LINUX` guard the files.

The new schema _may_ provide for a `compile` under the `configurations` (if they're under `buildOptions`), but this wouldn't really be viable until https://github.com/dotnet/cli/issues/3577 is fixed, and the `compile` sections (and any `buildOptions` property IMHO) get merged.
